DURBAN - The South African Air Force and an Air Mercy Services chopper were dispatched to a fatal crash involving 18 school children in Eshowe, northern KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. The crash, which took place on a rural road between Mandeni and Eshowe, claimed the life of a 17-year-old pupil. Seventeen others were injured. Paul Herbst, IPSS spokesman said six pupils were critically injured, eight others suffered moderate injuries while the rest escaped with minor injuries. “Owing to the severity of injuries and accessibility, the six critical patients were airlifted by the South African Airforce, using an Oryx helicopter. IPSS advanced life support paramedics worked to stabilise the patients onboard the aircraft,” said Herbst.  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
